relation.text: 'll never be Hector 'd by a Subject Anne D 4 th . November
1803 B . in my dreſsing Room . at ½ past 11 A Maria & I walk
went to bed ½ past 11 5 th - Novbr- 1783
Wednesday -- Had a Cold in my Limbs -- had hartshorn & tea & did not get up
came home ¼ past 11 o'Clock 6 th . Novbr . Thursday
Saturday for Mrs. Siddons she wld
Friday . Katherine Jackson , Groom to Mr Johnston came
sat in my Room ¼ of an hour & c & c Novbr . 8 th . 1783
Saturday . dreſs 'd for ye . day in a Habit -- breakfast in my dreſsing Room settled
was expected in Town on Monday
came home abt . 11 o'Clock . Fanny had call 'd when I was out Novbr . 10 th . Monday
went to bed ¼ past 12 o'Clock Novbr . 11 th . Tuesday
went to bed abt . 12 oClock Letter from Mrs. Jackson 12 Novbr . 1783
came to me for a short time
Saturday , I did so when I came
was brought to bed last Sunday
went to bed ½ after . Friday
told me that she was a sensible Woman & had been a friend of Saturday
went to bed abt . 12 . Chevalier Sagramoso had call 'd upon us in ye- Eveg . Monday
1783 London . Got up at 8 . Sr Wm . & I breakfasted
sent me word she had been in town some days
separated at 11 oClock Wedn . 19 th . Novbr . 1783
parted at ½ past 11 Novbr . 21 st . 1783
Friday Bullstrode Before breakfast I came up
wrote a letter to Dr : Solander Novbr . 22 d . Bullstrode Satry . 1783
told me her abt . her governeſs & c & c & c 2.3 d . Sunday
gave us an humoursome account of an her going hunting when she was 13 Years
will send for me Saty : 29 th . Novbr . 1783
her time . ye . day was mild as in June
s poſseſsion a Diary or Journal Thursday
